<title>USA: Handy &amp; Harman sets Dutch auction, shrs rise.</title>
<headline>Handy &amp; Harman sets Dutch auction, shrs rise.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Handy &amp; Harman said its board approved a Dutch auction tender offer for about 13 percent of its common shares, sending its stock up over seven percent on Tuesday.</p>
<p>The company said it will begin the bid for 1.8 million shares on October 24 and it will expire 20 buiness days later unless extended.</p>
<p>Under terms of the offer, Handy &amp; Harman will offer to purchase shares at between $17.50 and $20 each. It plans to fund the offer from cash on hand, sales of precious metals inventory and its existing long term credit facilities.</p>
<p>The stock rose 1-1/4 to 18-5/8.</p>
